  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nErigon exposes a number of metric to monitor the client; however, they are all completely undocumented and as a result, all but the most self-explanatory metrics become quite meaningless.\r\n\r\nAt the very least, each metric should be documented in the markdown docs, and hopefully also within the output (for example, prometheus allows for this to be documented).\r\n\r\nFor example, here's an example of some self-documented prometheus metrics produced by the `lighthouse` client:\r\n\r\n```text\r\n# HELP http_api_status_codes_total Count of HTTP status codes returned\r\n# TYPE http_api_status_codes_total counter\r\nhttp_api_status_codes_total{status=\"200 OK\"} 726\r\nhttp_api_status_codes_total{status=\"405 Method Not Allowed\"} 1\r\nhttp_api_status_codes_total{status=\"500 Internal Server Error\"} 2\r\n# HELP info_total Count of infos logged\r\n# TYPE info_total counter\r\ninfo_total 484\r\n# HELP libp2p_address_update_total Count of libp2p socked updated events (when our view of our IP address has changed)\r\n# TYPE libp2p_address_update_total counter\r\nlibp2p_address_update_total 1\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhile I would be happy to help with this, I don't know what most metrics mean myself.\r\n\r\n",
